<topic id="d3aAkz">
   <title>Variable and function names</title>
   <body>
      <p outputclass="Para">Name the variables and functions so the next developer understands them. Be descriptive and use meaningful names â€” clarity over brevity<i>.</i>
      </p>
      <p outputclass="Para">This will help us avoid writing functions like this:</p>
      <table>
         <tgroup cols="1">
            <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="90.16%"/>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>function div(x, y)) { const val = x / y; return val;}</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </table>
      <p outputclass="Para">And hopefully more like this:</p>
      <table>
         <tgroup cols="1">
            <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="90.16%"/>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <p>function divide(divident, divisor) {</p>
                     <p>  const quotient = divident / divisor;</p>
                     <p>  return quotient;</p>
                     <p>}</p>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </table>
   </body>
